  "prompt": "What can a mehanical engineer do after clearing SSC cgl?",
  "response": "After clearing the SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) exam, a mechanical engineer can pursue various government job opportunities:\n\n1. Direct Government Positions:\n- Junior Engineer (Civil/Mechanical)\n- Divisional Engineer\n- Technical Assistant\n- Inspector of Factories\n- Quality Control Inspector\n\n2. Central Government Departments:\n- Railways\n- Defense Organizations\n- Public Sector Undertakings (PSUs)\n- Ministry of Defense\n- DRDO\n- Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO)\n- Central Public Works Department (CPWD)\n- Survey of India\n\n3. Possible Job Roles:\n- Technical Maintenance\n- Project Management\n- Equipment Inspection\n- Design and Development\n- Technical Documentation\n- Procurement\n- Quality Assurance\n\n4. Tier-wise Opportunities:\n- Tier I: Lower-level administrative and technical positions\n- Tier II: Higher-level technical and administrative roles\n- Tier III: Selection for specialized technical positions\n\n5. Additional Career Paths:\n- Further competitive exams\n- Skill development courses\n- Higher education\n- Preparation for engineering-specific government examinations\n\nThe specific opportunities depend on the individual's tier, merit, and chosen department during the SSC CGL selection process.",
